paragraphs.title: Loading data and creating KV pair of poiID,categories
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.jena.riot.Lang
import com.typesafe.config.ConfigFactory
import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering.utils.DataProcessing
import net.sansa_stack.rdf.spark.io._


val input = "hdfs://namenode:8020/data/clusteringPipeline.nt"
val lang = Lang.NTRIPLES
val triples = spark.rdf(lang)(input)

val conf = ConfigFactory.load()
val data = new DataProcessing(spark = spark, conf = conf,triples)
val pois = data.pois
val poiCategorySet = pois.map(poi => (poi.poi_id, poi.categories.categories.toSet)).persist()

paragraphs.title: Applying K-means Clustering Algorithm on Categories
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering.algorithms.Encoder
import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering.algorithms.Kmeans
import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering._


val (avgVectorDF, word2Vec) = new Encoder().wordVectorEncoder(poiCategorySet, spark)

val db = triples.cluster(ClusteringAlgorithm.KMeans).asInstanceOf[Kmeans]

val avgVectorClusters = db.kmClustering(8,5,avgVectorDF,spark)

paragraphs.title: Save the output in the HDFS
paragraphs.text:
%spark

import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering.utils.Common
import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering.datatypes.{Cluster, Clusters, POI}

val assignments = avgVectorClusters.toList.sortBy { case (k, v) => v.length }
val assm=assignments.toArray
val poisKeyPair = pois.keyBy(f => f.poi_id).persist()

val clustersPois = Clusters(assignments.size, assignments.map(_._2.length).toArray, assm.map(f => Cluster(f._1, Common.join( spark.sparkContext,f._2, poisKeyPair))))

val newAssignment = assignments.map(f => (f._1, spark.sparkContext.parallelize(f._2).map(x => (x, x)).join(poisKeyPair).map(x => ( x._2._2.poi_id, x._2._2.categories, x._2._2.coordinate)).collect()))
val newAssignmentRDD = spark.sparkContext.parallelize(newAssignment)
val newAssignmentRDDTriple2 = newAssignmentRDD.map(cluster => (cluster._1, cluster._2.flatMap(poi =>
    List{(poi._1.toString,( poi._2.categories.mkString(";"))+",", poi._3.latitude, poi._3.longitude)}
    ).toList))
val res=newAssignmentRDDTriple2.flatMap(f=>(f._2.map(g=>(f._1,(f._1,g._1,g._2,g._3,g._4))))).groupByKey
val res1=res.map(f=>(f._2.toList))

paragraphs.title: Binding K-means clustering result from spark to angular
Reading K-means clustering output and preparing it for DBSCAN algo
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.{ Coordinate, Envelope, GeometryFactory, Point }

val geometryFactory = new GeometryFactory()

val dbParam = res1.collect.map(str => str.map{parts=>
   val poid=parts._1.toString
   val lat = parts._4
   val long= parts._5
   val point = geometryFactory.createPoint(new Coordinate(long, lat))
   point.setUserData(poid)
   point
})

paragraphs.title: Apply DBSCAN on each K-means cluster
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import net.sansa_stack.ml.spark.clustering.algorithms.DBSCAN
import scala.util.parsing.json._
import org.json4s.jackson.Serialization.write
import org.json4s._
import org.json4s.jackson.JsonMethods._
import com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.{ Coordinate, Envelope, GeometryFactory, Point }   
  
val dbfilter=dbparam.filter(f => f.size > 35) // NOTE: 35 takes time but if reduced it may raise a GeoSpark paritioning issue
case class Coordinate2(longitude: Double, latitude: Double)
case class Cluster2(cluster_id: String, cluster_id_kmeans:String,poi_in_cluster:  Array[Coordinate2])
case class Clusters1(numOfClusters: Int, clusterSizes:Array[Int], clusters: Array[Cluster2])

val broadcastRDD = spark.sparkContext.broadcast(dbfilter)
val convertRDD=broadcastRDD.value.map{case u=>spark.sparkContext.parallelize(u)}

val dbscan = triples.cluster(ClusteringAlgorithm.DBSCAN).asInstanceOf[DBSCAN]

val k = convertRDD.map(f => dbscan.dbclusters(f, 0.001, 2, spark))

val clusterIDPOIidPair = k.map(arr => arr.map(f => (f._1, f._2.map(g => (g._1,g._2.lat,g._2.lon)))).groupByKey())
val temp= clusterIDPOIidPair.reduce( _ ++ _ )


val col=temp.collect().toArray
val exp=col.map(f => (f._1,f._2.map(f => (f.length)).toArray)).toArray

def subsequenceT(a: String): String = {
    a.substring(0, 1)
}

def findTerm(gt: (String, Iterable[Array[(String, Double, Double)]])): Cluster2 = {
    val a=gt._1
    val c=gt._2.map(f => f.head).map(f => f._1).head
    val func=subsequenceT(c)
    val b=gt._2.flatMap(f => f.map(f => (Coordinate2(f._3,f._2))))
    (Cluster2(a,func,b.toArray))
}

val newdata=col.map(f => f._2.map(f => f.length).toArray).flatMap(f => f).toArray
val pois=Clusters1(exp.size, newdata,col.map(g => findTerm(g)))
